summary: You: Kylo Ren’s mask?! ITS BACK?! J J ABRAMS IS ABOUT TO BUST STAR WARS AND KYLO REN WILL NEVER GET THE PROMISED REDEMPTION ARC...
body:
You: Kylo Ren’s mask?! ITS BACK?! J J ABRAMS IS ABOUT TO BUST STAR WARS AND KYLO REN WILL NEVER GET THE PROMISED REDEMPTION ARC

Me, an intellectual: Kylo Ren’s mask is a symbol of him being isolated from the people he loves and the light side of the force. When Rey turned away from him, Kylo felt a need to retreat back into that isolation in order to protect himself. The mask isn’t a symbol of him embracing The Dark Side; it’s about him trying to hide his insecurity and fear now that he’s alone and the key to his redemption arc is him coming to terms with his fear, which is why he needs the mask. Because that embracing needs to come from within him, while he’s isolated, as opposed to from the world around him - he is the key to his own salvation

WHY DO YOU THINK THE CODE NAME FOR IT WAS BLACK DIAMOND

HES A DIAMOND IN THE ROUGH KIDS

The movies are metaphorical for stages in our lives: in 7 Kylo’s a confused child in adolescence, in 8 he’s a young man finding his own skin, and in 9 he’s having to face himself in order to grow as a person

BOOM SYMBOLISM DEEP THOUGHTS

summary: my blog header:  “please don't tag me in or ask me about the filming of Star Wars Ep IX, I don't want to know even the slightest...
caption:
my blog header:  “please don’t tag me in or ask me about the filming of Star Wars Ep IX, I don’t want to know even the slightest spoilers about it, and I know less than you do”

should I go off the internet for a year to avoid speculative scattershot spoiler anons? should I turn off anon? should I block anons who try to come to me with spoilers? it’s a real conundrum.

if I want to talk about it, I’ll talk about it on my own, ok? If I’m not talking about it, assume I’m not interested in knowing about it in the first place. I care 10000% more about the official marketing.

summary: Why KotOR II Is Overrated
title: Why KotOR II Is Overrated
body:
Knights of the Old Republic II–or just Kotor 2, as it’s known in fandom–is one of the most respected games in the Star Wars fandom. The more or less common consensus about it is that it was a bit underdeveloped but still very good (and you can always use Restored Content Mod). And anyway, it’s the best because of its story, not its gameplay.

I have no problem with this opinion, actually. I vaguely remember playing it in 2005, and I remember I kinda enjoyed it. But lately I decided to make use of a holiday discount and try replaying it. And…well, now I feel it was a mistake.

Keep Reading

title: Warme cadeaus voor koude winterdagen
body:
Warme cadeaus voor koude winterdagen

December is een geweldige maand. Het is de maand van feest, cadeaus en lekker eten, maar ook de maand van koude dagen, gure temperaturen en korte dagen. Een tijd om lekker in de relaxmodus te gaan en je warm aangekleed op de bank te nestelen. Veel pyjama-tijd dus, met warme sokken of pantoffels en natuurlijk een coole badjas. Wij hebben een paar hele stoere badjassen gevonden waar we helemaal…
